The term "Head" may refer to any of the following:

Items[edit | edit source]

Monster drops[edit | edit source]

  • Abyssal demon head, a drop from Abyssal demons that players can stuff and mount in their houses
  • Basilisk head, a drop from Basilisks that players can stuff and mount in their houses
  • Cockatrice head, a drop from Cockatrices that players can stuff and mount in their houses
  • Ensouled heads, dropped by various creatures across Gielinor. Can be re-animated to train prayer.
  • Kq head, a drop from the Kalphite Queen that players can stuff and mount in their houses
  • Kbd heads, a drop from the King Black Dragon that players can stuff and mount in their houses
  • Kurask head, a drop from Kurasks that players can stuff and mount in their houses
  • Vorkath's head, a drop from Vorkath and a component to make Ava's assembler

Holiday event items[edit | edit source]

  • Zombie head, an item available for the 2005 Halloween event
  • Jack lantern mask, commonly called a "pumpkin head", an item from the 2006 Halloween event
  • Chicken head

Quest items[edit | edit source]

  • Axe head, an item used during the "Another Slice of H.A.M." quest, and which formerly featured as part of a random event whilst woodcutting
  • Decapitated head, an item used as part of the "Creature of Fenkenstrain" quest
  • Decapitated head (The Fremennik Isles), an item used as part of The Fremennik Isles quest
  • Elvarg's head, an item used as part of Dragon Slayer I
  • Stone head, the head of a statue used during the Enakhra's Lament quest
  • Wizard's head, the severed head of Clarence, who was murdered prior to "The Hand in the Sand" quest

Other[edit | edit source]

  • Pickaxe head, which may came off the pickaxe handle as part of a random event whilst a player was mining. This random event was later removed

Non-player characters[edit | edit source]

  • Head (Temple Trekking), an enemy encounter in Temple Trekking
  • Head chef, the owner of the Cooks' Guild
  • Head thief, an NPC involved in the Monk's Friend quest
  • Head Mourner, the leader of the Death Guard
 This page is used to distinguish between articles with similar names.
If an internal link led you to this disambiguation page, you may wish to change the link to point directly to the intended article.
